When asking for code help, it’s infinitely easier if you share your code, ideally as a link to github (or similar). It’s also beneficial to provide descriptions of what you’ve already tried, any errors you get, etc.

That said, what you’re looking for is generally referred to as “SendableChooser”. You can find examples in the WPILib docs

This section of the PathPlanner Docs shows you how you can generate a sendable chooser with all of your auto scripts and send it to Shuffleboard.

https://pathplanner.dev/pplib-getting-started.html#create-a-sendablechooser-with-all-autos-in-project

The section I directly linked to is set up for all of the autonomous scripts you have written, however if you scroll through that page you will also find a section explaining how to only add the ones you want by name if you would prefer to do it via that method.
